records.addlTxt:
The State filed an Amended Information which amends count 1 to negligent operation of a motor vehicle, contrary to Section 941.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, fleeing an officer.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) Months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Continue and complete counseling with Dr. Burbach;
2) Defendant must surrender his cycle endorsement and not operate a motorcycle during the period of probation;
3) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 02-17-15 by 8:00 a.m.;
4) Spend an additional thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
The Court denies the request for expungement in this matter.
Amended Information.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Minutes.
